main event: A round object was observed off the ground that moved up and down rapidly and then disappeared. The observation lasted 3-4 minutes.
interesting points: The object moved in a 16 degree arc over about 1 mile.
There was no weather balloon activity in the area at the time.
The observer attempted to photograph the object and said they would provide copies to the Air Force if the photographs were revealing.
The Air Force staff intelligence officer concluded that the fact the object remained stationary for a long period of time eliminated the possibility of it being a 'plastic bag type UFO'.
photographs: yes, the observer attempted to photograph the object
